Fix AOT compatibility warnings in the following files in `/tmp/sv-78fbc3ade099409cac87a7f25b20b38c/before/`. Do NOT consult the `after/` directory.

## File 1: `ArmOperation.cs`
**Problem:** IL2087/IL2090 - `IsResource<T>()` uses reflection (`typeof(T).GetConstructor(...)` and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)`) on an unannotated type parameter `T`.

**Fix:** Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to `T` in `IsResource<T>()`. Then propagate the same annotation to callers `Rehydrate<T>()` and `RehydrateAsync<T>()`. These methods already have `where T : notnull` constraints - add the attribute there. You need `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` in the using block.

Specifically:
```csharp
private static bool IsResource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T>() where T : notnull
```
And similarly for `Rehydrate<T>` and `RehydrateAsync<T>`.

## File 2: `GenericOperationSource.cs`  
**Problem:** IL2087 - `typeof(T)` is passed to `ModelReaderWriter.Read(response.Content, typeof(T))` which requires `PublicConstructors | NonPublicConstructors`, and `Activator.CreateInstance(typeof(T), ...)` which requires `NonPublicConstructors`.

**Fix:** Add `[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)]` to the class type parameter `T`. Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` if not present.

```csharp
internal class GenericOperationSource<[DynamicallyAccessedMembers(DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.PublicConstructors | DynamicallyAccessedMemberTypes.NonPublicConstructors)] T> : IOperationSource<T>
```

## File 3: `Extensions/ArmClientBuilderExtensions.cs`
**Problem:** IL2026/IL3050 - calling `RegisterClientFactory` which has `[RequiresUnreferencedCode]` and `[RequiresDynamicCode]`.

**Fix:** Add both attributes to the `AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>` method (the second overload at around line 27). Add `using System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis;` if not present.

```csharp
[RequiresUnreferencedCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values is not supported with trimming. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
[RequiresDynamicCode("Binding strongly typed objects to configuration values requires generating dynamic code at runtime, for example instantiating generic types. Use the Configuration Binder Source Generator (EnableConfigurationBindingGenerator=true) instead.")]
public static IAzureClientBuilder<ArmClient, ArmClientOptions> AddArmClient<TBuilder, TConfiguration>(this TBuilder builder, TConfiguration configuration)
```

## File 4: `ArmEnvironment.cs`
**Problem:** IL2026/IL3050 at line 80 - `JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` in `ToString()`.

**Fix:** Replace `JsonSerializer.Serialize(this)` with manual JSON construction. `ArmEnvironment` has `Endpoint` (Uri) and `Audience` (string) and `DefaultScope` (string) properties. Write it manually:

```csharp
public override string ToString()
